=================
  About my-diff
=================
      2012
-----------------


**my-diff** analyzes two files and prints the lines that are different.
Essentially, it outputs a set of instructions for how to change one file in order 
to make it identical to the second file. It is my implementation of the unix/linux command called *diff*
It is free as in freedom, released under the GNU General Public License version 3:
this means you are free to use, distribute and modify the program for any porpuse,
as long as you provide the same freedoms when sharing it with others.
The program is intended to work on any POSIX-compliant operating system,
although it has only been tested on GNU/Linux.


