Building and Usage
------------------

In order to compile my-diff (assuming that ''make'' and ''gcc'' are available
on your system), simply run the command::

    $ make my-diff

An executable binary file called ''my-diff'' will be generated, which can be run
by typing::

    $ ./my-diff <file1> <file2>

where <file1> and <file2> are two plain text files.
The output generated is printed for the standard output and the rules follow 
for this are the same that the original Unix/linux command.